    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-12-05T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-12-05T13:00:00-05:00" n="497"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d497">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">121.5532/11: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-12-05T15:00:00-03:00"
                            >December 5, 1930—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 5—2:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>162. Department’s 94, December 3, 6 p.m. Since my telegram No. 161, December 5, 2
                        p.m.,<note n="26" xml:id="d497fn26">Not printed; see despatch No. 3475,
                        December 5, from the Ambassador in Brazil, <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi>
                    </note> transmits formal notice that the services of the Naval Mission will
                    terminate on January 31st next, I shall be gratified if Lieutenant Commander
                    Blandy’s appointment can be announced. The effect here will be beneficial.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morgan</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
